<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
 <head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Basketball Team Signup</title>
 </head>
 <body>
   <!--
   Add a form to the newteam.erb template and render it in the GET /newteam route.
   The form should have fields for: Team name ('name') Coach ('coach') Point Guard ('pg') Shooting Guard ('sg') Power Forward ('pf') Small Forward ('sf') Center ('c')
   When creating your form, your "Submit" button will need to be identified by an id attribute with value of "Submit".

   Handle form submission:
   Create a route that responds to a POST request at /team.
   Have the form send a POST request to this route.
   Upon submission, pass the submitted data to the team.erb template.
   -->
   <form action="/team" method="post">
     <label>Team Name: <input type="text" name="name" /></label>
     <br>
     <label>Coach: <input type="text" name="coach" /></label>
     <br>
     <label>Point Guard: <input type="text" name="pg" /></label>
     <br>
     <label>Shooting Guard: <input type="text" name="sg" /></label>
     <br>
     <label>Power Forward: <input type="text" name="pf" /></label>
     <br>
     <label>Small Forward: <input type="text" name="sf" /></label>
     <br>
     <label>Center: <input type="text" name="c" /></label>
     <br><br>
     <input type="submit" id="Submit" />
   </form>
   
 </body>
</html>
